            <div class="card">
              <div class="card-block">

                <h3 class="card-title">Tips & Tricks</h3>
                
                <ul class="list-icons list-checklist">
                  <li>The Roles Model
                    <ul>
                      <li>Abstract Roles</li>
                      <li>Widget Roles</li>
                      <li>Document Structure</li>
                      <li>Landmark Roles</li>
                    </ul>
                  </li>
                  <li>Supported States and Properties</li>
                  <li>Managing Focus</li>
                  <li>Conformance</li>
                </ul>

                <h4 class="heading-s">What Is ARIA?</h4>              
                <ul class="list-icons list-checklist">
                  <li>Accessible Rich Internet Applications</li>
                  <li>Without ARIA it's impossible for AT to fully understand all components</li>
                  <li>ARIA is to provide information for the A11Y APIs</li>
                  <li>ARIA changes everything</li>
                  <li>For interactive widgets, and applications</li>
                  <li>The work of web accessibility advocates</li>
                  <li>For names, roles, states and properties</li>
                  <li>ARIA Allows Real-Time Live Announcements</li>
                </ul>
                
               <h4 class="heading-s">ARIA Concepts</h4>
                <ul class="list-icons list-checklist">
                  <li>
                   ARIA allows you to communicate the following information to screen readers:
                    <ul>
                      <li>Labels</li>
                      <li>Roles</li>
                      <li>States</li>
                      <li>Properties</li>
                      <li>Relationships</li>
                    </ul>
                  </li>
                  <li>ARIA is Useful Only to Assistive Technologies</li>
                  <li>ARIA is Not a Programming Language</li>
                </ul>

