    <section class="full-cover bg-grey" role="region" id="name-label" aria-labelledby="title-name-label">
      <div class="container">

        <h2 class="full-cover-title" id="title-name-label">Name Vs. Label</h2>
        
        <div class="text-right to-top">
          <a href="#totop" class="link-ts"><span>To Top</span></a>
        </div>

        <div class="row">

          <div class="col-md-6">

            <div class="card">
              <div class="card-block">

                <h3 class="card-title">Checklist - Deque</h3>

                <h4 class="heading-s">Label Examples category</h4>
                <p>None documented</p>
                
                <h4 class="heading-s">Download Summary & Checklist</h4>
                <p>None documented</p>

              </div>
              <div>
                <a href="https://dequeuniversity.com/class/custom-widgets2/concepts/name" class="link-plug-on">
                  <span class="icon icon-college icon-xl icon-gray-dark mr-2" aria-hidden="true"></span> ARIA Name - Deque University</a>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
              <div class="card-block">

                <h3 class="card-title">Tips & Tricks</h3>
                
                <h4 class="heading-s">Non-ARIA Names and Labels</h4>
                <ul class="list-icons list-checklist">
                  <li>The <code>&lt;label&gt;</code> tag designates the label for a form <code>&lt;input&gt;</code> element.</li>
                  <li>The <code>&lt;legend&gt;</code> labels <code>&lt;fieldset&gt;</code> elements (groups of form elements).</li>
                  <li>The <code>&lt;th&gt;</code> tag designates a table header cell (as opposed to <code>&lt;td&gt;</code> for table data cells).</li>
                  <li>The text inside the opening and closing <code>&lt;button&gt;</code> elements is the label for that button.</li>
                  <li>The <code>value</code> attribute on a submit button serves as the label for that button.</li>
                  <li>The <code>alt</code> attribute serves as the name, or text replacement, for an image.</li>
                  <li>The <code>&lt;title&gt;</code> tag designates the name of a web page.</li>
                  <li>The <code>title</code> attribute designates the name of an <code>&lt;iframe&gt;</code> element.</li>
                  <li>A visible label for a component not programmatically related like adjecent button for an input or an icon with screen reader only text</li>
                </ul>
                
                <h4 class="heading-s">Descriptions - Aria-describedby</h4>
                <ul class="list-icons list-checklist">
                  <li>The Purpose is to provide extra information</li>
                  <li>Works in the same way as aria-labelledby</li>
                  <li>Refers to the id of another object</li>
                  <li>More verbose, can contain entire paragraphs, best to keep text brief</li>
                  <li>Support in Jaws very good</li>
                  <li>Long delay VoiceOver OSX, but can be shortened</li>
                  <li>Short delay VoiceOver iOS</li>
                  <li>Isn't read on most types of elements (div, paragraph, list item, etc.) by either NVDA or VoiceOver</li>
                  <li>Placing same elements inside an application region, NVDA and VoiceOver on Mac OSX (not iOS) will read them</li>
                </ul>

              </div>
            </div>

          </div>

          <div class="col-md-6">

